Doctors would not estimate when
Pittsburgh Penguins captain  Sidney Crosby  would return to the
 National Hockey League  after suffering a concussion in January.  Doctors said they anticipated that he would play again.
Crosby and doctors appeared at a news conference in Pittsburgh.  To contact the reporter on this story:
